lenders.name: Liz
lenders.occupational_info:
I am a 23 year old amateur photographer starting my masters degree in counseling psychology. I am inspired to make a difference in the world, and though this may be a small step, I'm hoping to do so through my photography. 100% of the money I receive through selling my photographs will be used in microloans through Kiva, benefiting entrepreneurs in less wealthy regions in beginning their own businesses and thus providing them with the resources to support themselves and their communities.

I will use my photography website (www.Lcato.zenfolio.com) to keep my clients updated on the amount of money raised and the specific individuals we will be aiding together. I am overwhelmed with excitement over the potential of this business and what it could do for numerous people and their local economies! I understand I am an amateur and still learning the art of capturing the best image possible, and I also have limited photographing opportunities. Because of these facts, I know it may be unrealistic to hope that Liz Cato Photography becomes large enough to inspire others into doing similar things, but any little bit will be helping someone, which is what truly matters.

Every single photo sold will be beneficial. They are fairly inexpensive compared to competition, thus I hope you consider the advantage you will be providing another individual in beginning their business when you think about buying from my website. My job is to provide you with a variety of photographs that will appeal to significant number of individuals, and I will do my best to perform to your standards. I appreciate so very much any purchases you choose to make!

Liz Cato Photography guarantees that 100% of profits from the products available for sale www.Lcato.zenfolio.com are used in the investment of microloans through Kiva, including the loan money paid back to the donor by the recipient of the donation loan.
